<p>Hello everyone, I've been a fan of the SCP universe since around 2012. Mostly, I have been reading and listening to readings of entries and tales, but I'd like to take a more active role in the community going forward. I think this whole thing is really a beautiful manifestation of the collective imagination of so many people, and I plan on contributing in some way. I want to be a part of it. I will probably write an article or two, and be around to see developments in the state of this community.</p>
<p>My hobbies include learning Esperanto, tabletop RPGs when I have the time, my garden, reading, and writing cool programs when I have ideas. I plan on learning Spanish soon. My favorite album right now is TFS - A Laughing Death in Meatspace or The Caretaker - An Empty Bliss Beyond This World. The sound that always puts me in a good mood is music. Kinda a copout answer, but I can't really think of anything more mood-lifting auditorially than that. Ĝis la revido! (that means 'until next time' in Esperanto)</p>

