<p><strong>Why/how I joined the site</strong>. Hi everyone! I found out about the site through YouTube suggestions (i think starting with either Fredrik Knudsen or the Internet Historian, then TheVolgun, and eventually the Exploring The SCP series). After watching a lot of videos and reading a bunch of entries, I became really impressed with the creativity, writing talent, and story telling ability of a lot of the contributors here, and decided I wanted to be a part of that. You all have an incredible writing project going on, and I feel like this could be a great way for me to develop creative writing skills, explore some cool metaphysical concepts, work on stretching my creative limits, and with some development, hopefully contribute something that can entertain others as much as I've been entertained.</p>
<p><strong>What I plan to do</strong>. I'll probably spend a lot of time lurking in the SCP articles, tales, and workshops for a while, but I would definitely like to try writing at some point. I feel like this could be a great place for me to get the kind of criticism and develop as a writer.</p>
<p><strong>Any concerns or worries about the site you have?</strong> It will probably take a while for me to figure out the chat system. Also, trying to figure out how to create meaningful narratives in a universe without narrative.</p>

							</div>

								
					
